<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880823-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Union Carbide Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ALD UK </CO><TEXT>   Allied-Signal Inc. and Union Carbide Corp. said they completed the formation of a joint venture to supply technology, products, engineered systems and services to petroleum, petrochemical and natural gas industries. Terms weren't disclosed.    The new business, which will be called UOP, combines Union Carbide's Catalysts, Absorbents andamp; Process Systems business with Allied-Signal's UOP Inc. unit, which provides process technology.    The units of Allied-Signal and Danbury, Conn.-based Union Carbide have combined annual sales of about $600 million. Allied-Signal, based in Morris Township, N.J., operates businesses in engineered materials, aerospace and automotive parts. Union Carbide has its principal businesses in chemicals and plastics, industrial gases and carbon products. </TEXT></DOC>